I wanted to use EOL operation (in an ETL context) to convert a certain EnumLiteral into another EnumLiteral and tried to do this with:

example:
operation convertLiteral(someInputLiteral) {
  if(someInputLiteral == input!x::y::z.Ordering.Up) {
    return output!a::b::c.ConvertedOrdering.UpLeft;
  } 
  return output!a::b::c.ConvertedOrdering.DownRight;
}

which led to the exception:
Undefined variable, type or model: 'input!Ordering', which is misleading, as the Enum does exist, but it just cannot be used in this way. A better exception would be to show how to use this enum.

The correct syntax is (can also be found in the Epsilon book):

operation convertLiteral(someInputLiteral) {
  if(someInputLiteral == input!x::y::z.Ordering#Up) {
    return output!a::b::c.ConvertedOrdering#UpLeft;
  } 
  return output!a::b::c.ConvertedOrdering#DownRight;
}

