It seems that GMF exhibits a bug when two (or more) affixed nodes are created on the same parent node. This bug only seems to affect nodes whose "affixed parent side" property in the GMF graph is set to Direction#NSEW. The UML2Tools team seem to have found this issue too (see #317478, for example).

To recreate:
(1) - Use the Emfatic from the affixed nodes example: http://www.eclipse.org/epsilon/doc/articles/eugenia-affixed-nodes/

(2) - Create a component in the generated editor and two ports. Creating the second port will result in a strange placement (in the top-left of the editor), and possibly an exception too. Saving the diagram will corrupt it, and it cannot be reopened.

The workaround seems to be to use a value other than Direction#NSEW for the affixed node. The following polishing transformation, placed in an Ecore2GMF.eol, file seems to fix the issue when using EuGENia:

for (affixedNode in GmfGraph!Node.all.select(n|n.affixedParentSide == GmfGraph!Direction#NSEW)) {
	affixedNode.affixedParentSide = GmfGraph!Direction#NORTH;
}

This has been fixed for a while. You just need to set label.placement to "none":

@gmf.node(label.placement="none")
class Foo {}

See the Eugenia reference here:

http://eclipse.org/epsilon/doc/articles/eugenia-gmf-tutorial/

