Build ID: M20071023-1652

Steps To Reproduce:
The following EOL is inconsistent. The first two statements return true, and the last two return false.

-- These return true
'foo'.isTypeOf(String).println();
'foo'.isKindOf(String).println();

-- These return false!
String.isType('foo').println();
String.isKind('foo').println(); 


More information:

Up to 0.8.5, the delete statement accepts only a single model element e.g.

delete EClass.all.random(); -- deletes a random EClass

If we want to delete a collection of model elements, combining delete with a for loop doesn't work due to a (reasonable) concurrent modification exception e.g.

for (c in EClass.all) {
  delete c;
}

Therefore, delete should also accept collections of model elements e.g.

delete EClass.all;

The Epsilon book would also need to be updated accordingly.

