This is a bug in the EGL preprocessor. A workaround is to make sure there are no empty lines between two operations in the same file. For example:

[%
operation foo(){
}
%]

[%
operation bar(){
}
%]

will not work (and since 0.8.4 it will also show an error marker in the EGL editor), but:

[%
operation foo(){
}
%]
[%
operation bar(){
}
%]

will work fine. I'm putting this in the todo list for 0.8.5.

